Code = a recipe with forks. Here's the pattern:

```
if (someCondition) {
    // runs when condition is TRUE
} else {
    // runs when condition is FALSE
}
```

For your case: `if (hasLocationPermission) { saveGpsPosition() } else { showManualEntry() }`. One branch runs, the other doesn't. Never both. The app picks based on what's true RIGHT NOW.

You can chain them: `if … else if … else if … else`. But usually two branches is enough.

